{
  "analysis": "The current build script calculated a fusion protein of 1026 aa / 3078 nt, exceeding the 3000 nt limit, so /app/gblock.txt was not written. The components are verified: Clover (FPbase/RCSB 5WJ2, ex 505 nm), mCherry (FPbase/RCSB 2H5Q, em 610 nm), SNAP-tag (3KZY), DHFR from plasmid, and HER2 as the antibody target. To satisfy length, we should use a compact HER2 trastuzumab epitope fragment (residues 529–625, 97 aa) while keeping 10 aa GS linkers, then codon-optimize and validate all constraints.",
  "plan": "Run a revised build script that uses HER2 residues 528:625 as the antibody binder, keeps component order antibody_binder–donor_Clover–DHFR–acceptor_mCherry–molecule_binder_SNAP, removes N-terminal methionines, uses 10 aa GS linkers only between components, codon-optimizes with 50 nt GC-window repair, validates length ≤3000 nt, GC 30–70% in all windows, exact translation, no start/stop codons, no terminal linkers, and writes /app/gblock.txt if valid. Then check the output file.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('/app/build_gblock.py')\ns=p.read_text()\ns=s.replace('antibody_binder_raw=her2[479:652]', 'antibody_binder_raw=her2[528:625]')\ns=s.replace(\"print('HER2 domain IV raw len', len(antibody_binder_raw), antibody_binder_raw[:40])\", \"print('HER2 trastuzumab epitope raw len', len(antibody_binder_raw), antibody_binder_raw[:40])\")\np.write_text(s)\nprint('updated build_gblock.py for HER2 epitope 528:625')\nPY\npython3 /app/build_gblock.py\n",
      "duration": 10.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo '--- gblock status ---'; ls -l /app/gblock.txt 2>/dev/null || true; if [ -f /app/gblock.txt ]; then wc -c /app/gblock.txt; fi\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
